                                                                    Ruud van Nistelrooy and Mohamed Salah as the men to
                                                                    have scored most goals for a Premier League club
                                                                    across all competitions in a single campaign.</p>
                                                                <p>He finished his incredible debut season with 52 goals
                                                                    in 53 games and had a fairytale ending as he was
                                                                    part of the Pep Guardiola’s Treble-winning team,
